---
// src/components/FootnoteSection.astro
//
// Marks the boundary between the essay body and the footnote items at
// the bottom of an essay. Renders two pieces:
//
//   1. A decorative asterism divider (⁂) — a typographic ornament
//      indicating a stronger section break than the in-body `---` rules
//      (which are styled to be invisible). The asterism is the
//      universal print convention for "section apparatus follows".
//
//   2. A "Footnotes" label, set in body serif at heading scale. This
//      is rendered as a <p>, NOT an <h2>. The deliberate choice keeps
//      it OUT of the rehype-slug heading tree, which means it never
//      appears in the auto-generated table of contents. Future essays
//      that DO have body H2s will get a clean ToC of just those H2s,
//      with no "Footnotes" entry polluting the list.
//
// Usage in MDX (assumes the component is registered via the
// `components` prop in src/pages/essays/[...slug].astro):
//
//   ...essay body ends with the closing question.
//
//   <FootnoteSection />
//
//   <Footnote id="1">First footnote text.</Footnote>
//   <Footnote id="2">Second footnote text.</Footnote>
//
// The component takes no props. If we ever need to vary the label
// text (e.g., "Notes" vs "References"), add an optional `label` prop
// then; v1 is fixed at "Footnotes" because that's what these are.
//
// Styles for both the asterism and the label live in
// EssayLayout.astro's <style is:global> block, alongside the other
// .essay__body styles. They have to be global because the component's
// output is rendered inside MDX content, where scoped styles don't
// reach.
---

<div class="essay-asterism" role="separator" aria-hidden="true">⁂</div>
<p class="essay-footnote-heading">Footnotes</p>
